# **Enhanced "Infinite Folder" Prank with Virus Note & Hidden Folders**

Here's the complete step-by-step Python prank with all your requested features:

## **Step 1: Install Python**
Make sure you have Python installed from [python.org](https://www.python.org/)

## **Step 2: Create the Script (`infinite_folders_prank.py`)**
```python
import os
import time
from threading import Thread

# ===== CONFIG =====
ROOT_FOLDER = "C:\\INFECTED_FOLDERS"  # Where the prank starts
DELAY_SECONDS = 0.1                   # Speed of folder creation
STOP_AFTER_MINUTES = 1                 # Auto-stop after X minutes (0=infinite)
HIDE_FOLDERS = True                    # Make folders hidden
ADD_VIRUS_NOTE = True                  # Add fake virus warning
# ==================

def create_infinite_folders():
    """Creates never-ending nested folders"""
    current_path = ROOT_FOLDER
    os.makedirs(current_path, exist_ok=True)
    
    # Add virus note if enabled (with proper encoding)
    if ADD_VIRUS_NOTE:
        virus_note = os.path.join(current_path, "!!!WARNING!!!.txt")
        with open(virus_note, "w", encoding="utf-8") as f:  # FIX: Added encoding
            f.write("!!! YOUR FILES HAVE BEEN FOLDERIZED !!!\n\n")
            f.write("This is the work of the INFINITE FOLDER VIRUS!\n")
            f.write("To remove this virus, you must:\n")
            f.write("1. Bring me 10 pieces of candy\n")
            f.write("2. Say 'I believe in folder ghosts'\n")
            f.write("3. Restart your computer 3 times\n\n")
            f.write("Good luck! >:D")  # Replaced emoji with ASCII
    
    # Hide the root folder if enabled
    if HIDE_FOLDERS:
        os.system(f'attrib +h "{ROOT_FOLDER}"')
    
    # Start creating infinite folders
    while True:
        try:
            current_path = os.path.join(current_path, "ANOTHER_FOLDER")
            os.makedirs(current_path, exist_ok=True)
            time.sleep(DELAY_SECONDS)
        except:
            break

def main():
    print(f"Launching Infinite Folder Prank at: {ROOT_FOLDER}")
    print("Warning: This will create thousands of folders!")
    print("Press CTRL+C to stop early.\n")
    
    # Run in background thread
    Thread(target=create_infinite_folders, daemon=True).start()
    
    # Auto-stop timer
    if STOP_AFTER_MINUTES > 0:
        print(f"Will stop after {STOP_AFTER_MINUTES} minutes...")
        time.sleep(STOP_AFTER_MINUTES * 60)
    else:
        print("Running FOREVER until stopped...")
        while True:
            time.sleep(1)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    try:
        main()
    except KeyboardInterrupt:
        print("\nPrank stopped by user!")
    finally:
        print(f"Created folders up to: {ROOT_FOLDER}\\ANOTHER_FOLDER\\...")
        print("To delete: rmdir /s /q", f'"{ROOT_FOLDER}"')
```

## **Step 3: Run the Prank**
1. Open Command Prompt as Administrator
2. Navigate to your script location
3. Run:
   ```cmd
   python infinite_folders_prank.py
   ```

## **What Happens**
1. Creates hidden folder `C:\INFECTED_FOLDERS` (if you have admin rights)
2. Adds a scary "virus" warning note
3. Generates endless subfolders named `ANOTHER_FOLDER`
4. Stops after 2 minutes (configurable)

## **How to Remove**
1. Open Command Prompt as Admin
2. Run:
   ```cmd
   rmdir /s /q "C:\INFECTED_FOLDERS"
   ```

